830: :::{prf:definition} Valid Noise Measure
831: :label: def-valid-noise-measure
832: A kernel $\mathcal P_\sigma$ (and analogously $\mathcal Q_\delta$) is valid if it is Feller and satisfies:
833: - Bounded second moment in $\mathcal Y$ with constant $M_{\mathrm{pert}}^2$ (as used in the perturbation continuity bounds);
834: - Boundary regularity assumptions required by the status‑continuity theorem (Section 14);
